4. The software is now used in all public clinics and many private clinics across the country. The project includes programmes for monitoring communicable, non-communicable and mental health disease.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 18pt; line-height: 20pt;\\\"><b>Madagascar | <\\/b>We also partner with the WHO in Madagascar, which is our largest implementation with data reporting from 693 sites. The work focuses on tracking communicable disease - especially endemic Plague. Special tools have been built for contact tracing and reporting of plague cases.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 18pt; line-height: 20pt;\\\"><b>Somalia | <\\/b>Our software in Somalia is used by the local ministries of health, and supported by UNICEF, to monitor Health and Nutrition in response to the 2017 Somalian drought. In addition to monitoring communicable diseases, the project has included facility monitoring and prescription and supply chain monitoring.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size: 18pt; line-height: 20pt;\\\"><b>Technology | <\\/b>We pick up new technologies quickly, but have particular experience in working with: Open Data Kit, DHIS2, OpenMRS, Linux, Python, Java, Docker, PostgreSQL, Amazon Web Services, NGINX, Javascript, and HTML\\/CSS.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":1,\"catid\":\"2\",\"created\":\"2018-05-22 09:29:53\",\"created_by\":\"245\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2018-05-23 13:57:42\",\"modified_by\":\"245\",\"checked_out\":\"245\",\"checked_out_time\":\"2018-05-23 13:57:37\",\"publish_up\":\"2018-05-22 09:29:53\",\"publish_down\":\"0000-00-00 00:00:00\",\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"